- 1.0.0 | Mar 05 2026:
  [New] Telegram delivery: sendMessage (_alert_telegram_message) with
      MarkdownV2 parse mode, sendDocument (_alert_telegram_document) with
      file upload and optional caption; router _alert_deliver_telegram
      with env var config (ALERT_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, ALERT_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID)
  [New] Telegram API helper (_alert_telegram_api): shared curl -K config
      file pattern keeping bot token out of process listing (chmod 600
      temp file, rm after use); response validation with error extraction
  [New] Telegram channel handler (_alert_handle_telegram) with built-in
      channel registration (disabled by default)
  [New] Test suite 05-telegram.bats: 35 tests covering API helper security
      (token not in args, config file permissions, cleanup), sendMessage,
      sendDocument, delivery router, handler, and channel registration
  [New] Slack delivery: webhook (_alert_slack_webhook), bot API
      (_alert_slack_post_message), 3-step file upload (_alert_slack_upload);
      router _alert_deliver_slack with ALERT_SLACK_MODE webhook|bot
  [New] HTTP utility: _alert_curl_post shared POST helper with configurable
      timeouts (ALERT_CURL_TIMEOUT, ALERT_CURL_MAX_TIME), stderr capture,
      and error detail logging
  [New] URL validation: _alert_validate_url for http/https URL checking
  [New] Slack channel handler (_alert_handle_slack) with built-in channel
      registration (disabled by default)
  [New] Test suite 04-slack.bats: tests covering HTTP utilities, Slack
      webhook, bot API, 3-step upload, delivery router, handler, and
      channel registration
  [New] Test helper: alert_create_curl_mock and alert_create_curl_routing_mock
      for response-aware and multi-step API curl mocking
  [New] Channel registry: alert_channel_register, alert_channel_enable,
      alert_channel_disable, alert_channel_enabled with parallel indexed
      arrays and _alert_channel_find lookup helper
  [New] Multi-channel dispatch: alert_dispatch with per-channel template
      rendering (.text.tpl/.message.tpl/.html.tpl), custom.d/ override
      support, comma-separated channel filtering, and fault-tolerant
      dispatch (continues after individual channel failures)
  [New] Email channel handler: _alert_handle_email wrapper bridging
      standardized handler interface to _alert_deliver_email with
      ALERT_EMAIL_TO and ALERT_EMAIL_FORMAT env var config
  [New] Built-in email channel registration at source time (disabled
      by default; consumers enable via alert_channel_enable "email")
  [New] Test suite 03-registry.bats: 36 tests covering channel
      registration, enable/disable, dispatch loop, template rendering,
      channel filtering, error propagation, and temp file cleanup
  [New] MIME builder: _alert_build_mime (multipart/alternative with base64
      HTML part, ALERT_ boundary prefix, RFC 5321 compliant line lengths)
  [New] Email delivery: _alert_email_local (mail/sendmail with format-based
      routing and graceful fallback), _alert_email_relay (curl SMTP with
      TLS auto-detection and optional auth), _alert_deliver_email (router:
      ALERT_SMTP_RELAY → relay path, else → local MTA)
  [New] Test suite 02-email.bats: 29 tests covering MIME builder, local MTA,
      SMTP relay, delivery router, fallback chains, and error propagation
  [New] Mock binary infrastructure in alert-common.bash: alert_mock_setup and
      alert_create_mock for testing delivery functions without real binaries
  [New] Template engine: _alert_tpl_render (awk-based {{VAR}} substitution,
      mawk-compatible) and _alert_tpl_resolve (custom.d/ override resolution)
  [New] Escaping functions: _alert_html_escape (HTML entities via sed),
      _alert_json_escape (JSON string escaping via parameter expansion),
      _alert_telegram_escape (MarkdownV2 19-char set via sed),
      _alert_slack_escape (mrkdwn &amp; entity escaping via sed)
  [New] Test suite 01-core.bats: 33 tests covering all 6 functions with
      negative/false-positive tests for escape ordering and token matching
  [New] Project scaffolding: library skeleton, batsman test infrastructure,
      9-OS CI matrix, scaffold validation tests
